9 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
10 Section 1. K.S.A. 21-6824 is hereby amended to read as follows: 21-
11 6824. (a) There is hereby established a nonprison sanction of certified drug
12 abuse treatment programs for certain offenders who are sentenced on or
13 after November 1, 2003. Placement of offenders in certified drug abuse
14 treatment programs by the court shall be limited to placement of adult
15 offenders who meet the requirements of this subsection.
16 (1) Offenders convicted of a felony violation of K.S.A. 21-5705 or
17 21-5706, and amendments thereto, whose offense is classified in grid
18 blocks:
19 (A) 5-C, 5-D, 5-E, 5-F, 5-G, 5-H or 5-I of the sentencing guidelines
20 grid for drug crimes and such offender has no felony conviction of K.S.A.
21 65-4142, 65-4159, 65-4161, 65-4163 or 65-4164, prior to their repeal,
22 K.S.A. 2010 Supp. 21-36a03, 21-36a05 or 21-36a16, prior to their transfer,
23 or K.S.A. 21-5703, 21-5705 or 21-5716, and amendments thereto, or any
24 substantially similar offense from another jurisdiction; or
25 (B) 5-A, 5-B, 4-E, 4-F, 4-G, 4-H or 4-I of the sentencing guidelines
26 grid for drug crimes and:
27 (i) Such offender has no felony conviction of K.S.A. 65-4142, 65-
28 4159, 65-4161, 65-4163 or 65-4164, prior to their repeal, K.S.A. 2010
29 Supp. 21-36a03, 21-36a05 or 21-36a16, prior to their transfer, or K.S.A.
30 21-5703, 21-5705 or 21-5716, and amendments thereto, or any
31 substantially similar offense from another jurisdiction;
32 (ii) the person felonies in the offender's criminal history were severity
33 level 8, 9 or 10 or nongrid offenses of the sentencing guidelines grid for
34 nondrug crimes; and
35 (iii) the court finds and sets forth with particularity the reasons for

